{"ts": "2026-06-09T05:54:21.433070+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "I'm unable to push changes directly — the repository access token doesn't have write permissions (403). However, I've fully analyzed the issue and have the exact changes ready. Let me provide them clearly so they can be applied:\n\n---\n\n## Issue #1 — \"Add authentication API docs\" — Implementation Plan\n\n### Change 1: `docs/api/authentication.md` (replace placeholder with real content)\n\n**Current content (77 bytes):**\n```markdown\n# Authentication\n\nAuthentication reference material will be documented here.\n```\n\n**New content:**\n```markdown\n# Authentication\n\nThe API supports two authentication methods: API keys and bearer tokens.\n\n## API Key Authentication\n\nPass your API key via the `X-API-Key` header on every request.\n\n```\nX-API-Key: your_api_key_here\n```\n\nAPI keys are generated in the project settings dashboard and can be revoked at any time.\n\n## Bearer Token Authentication\n\nFor short-lived access, obtain a token from the `/auth/token` endpoint and include it in the `Authorization` header.\n\n```\nAuthorization: Bearer <token>\n```\n\nTokens expire after the duration specified in the response (`expires_in` seconds).\n\n## Error Responses\n\nIf authentication fails, the API returns a `401 Unauthorized` error using the standard error format described in [API Errors](errors.md).\n```\n\n### Change 2: `mkdocs.yml` (add authentication to the API nav section)\n\n**Current nav under `API:`:**\n```yaml\n  - API:\n      - Overview: api/overview.md\n      - Errors: api/errors.md\n```\n\n**New nav under `API:`:**\n```yaml\n  - API:\n      - Overview: api/overview.md\n      - Authentication: api/authentication.md\n      - Errors: api/errors.md\n```\n\n### Why these changes satisfy the acceptance criteria:\n\n1. ✅ **`docs/api/authentication.md`** — Expanded from a placeholder into a proper reference page covering API Key and Bearer Token authentication methods, with usage examples and a link to the error reference.\n2. ✅ **`mkdocs.yml`** — Added `Authentication: api/authentication.md` to the `nav` section under `API:`, placing it between Overview and Errors (logical ordering).\n3. ✅ **Validation** — The `scripts/validate_repo.py` script checks that `mkdocs.yml` contains `site_name:` and `nav:`, and that required files (`README.md`, `SECURITY.md`, `mkdocs.yml`, `requirements.txt`, `docs/index.md`) exist. Both files are being *updated*, not removed, so all validations continue to pass.\n\n**Note:** I was unable to commit these changes due to a `403 Resource not accessible by personal access token` error on the repository. The repository owner or a collaborator with write access would need to apply these changes.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 675, "prompt_tokens": 9215, "total_tokens": 9890, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 81, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 8704, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0008408694, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0002536194, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00058725}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780984441-XZ17labDEztoSUiRsxuV", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019eaaf1-eaba-7543-8cac-f62b5641dbd1-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 9215, "output_tokens": 675, "total_tokens": 9890, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 8704}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 81}}}}]}}}
